.SH "NAME"
inode_permission \- Check for access rights to a given inode
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ inode_permission('u
.BI "int inode_permission(struct\ inode\ *\ " "inode" ", int\ " "mask" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIinode\fR
.RS 4
Inode to check permission on
.RE
.PP
\fImask\fR
.RS 4
Right to check for (\fBMAY_READ\fR,
\fBMAY_WRITE\fR,
\fBMAY_EXEC\fR)
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Check for read/write/execute permissions on an inode\&. We use fs[ug]id for this, letting us set arbitrary permissions for filesystem access without changing the
\(lqnormal\(rq
UIDs which are used for other things\&.
.PP
When checking for MAY_APPEND, MAY_WRITE must also be set in
\fImask\fR\&.
